description: Andy Dufresne, a banker sentenced to life in Shawshank State Penitentiary, forms a friendship with inmate Red and finds solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.
title: The Shawshank Redemption

description: The aging patriarch of the Corleone crime family transfers control of his clandestine empire to his reluctant son Michael, but betrayal and violence loom.
title: The Godfather

description: Dom Cobb, a skilled thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology, is offered a chance for redemption: plant an idea instead of stealing one.
title: Inception

description: The lives of two mob hitmen, a boxer, a gangster’s wife, and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.
title: Pulp Fiction

description: When the Joker emerges in Gotham City, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.
title: The Dark Knight

description: The presidencies of Kennedy and Johnson, the Vietnam War, and other events unfold through the perspective of Forrest Gump, a man with a low IQ but good intentions.
title: Forrest Gump

description: An insomniac office worker and a devil‑may‑care soap maker form an underground fight club that evolves into something much, much more.
title: Fight Club

description: In German-occupied Poland during World War II, businessman Oskar Schindler gradually becomes concerned for his Jewish workforce after witnessing their persecution.
title: Schindler's List

description: A meek Hobbit from the Shire and eight companions set out on a journey to destroy the One Ring and save Middle-earth from the Dark Lord Sauron.
title: The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring

description: Luke Skywalker joins forces with a Jedi Knight, a cocky pilot, a Wookiee, and two droids to save the galaxy from the Empire’s world‑destroying battle station.
title: Star Wars: Episode IV – A New Hope

description: A computer hacker learns about the true nature of his reality and his role in the war against its controllers.
title: The Matrix

description: A former Roman General sets out to exact vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and sent him into slavery.
title: Gladiator

description: A team of explorers travel through a wormhole in space in an attempt to ensure humanity’s survival.
title: Interstellar

description: Lion prince Simba and his father are targeted by his bitter uncle, who wants to ascend the throne himself.
title: The Lion King

description: A seventeen‑year‑old aristocrat falls in love with a kind but poor artist aboard the luxurious, ill‑fated R.M.S. Titanic.
title: Titanic
